.TH RMDIR(1),User Commands,RMDIR(1)

.SH NAME
rmdir - remove directories

.SH SYNOPSIS
rmdir directory ...

.SH DESCRIPTION
rmdir removes each named directory.
At least one operand is required.

A directory must be empty to be removed.
rmdir does not recursively delete contents.

.SH DIAGNOSTICS
rmdir: missing operand - no arguments were given.

Error deleting directory 'X' - the directory could not be removed (not empty, does not exist, not a directory, etc.).
rmdir continues with any remaining operands after reporting the error.

.SH EXIT STATUS
0: No operands were missing.
rmdir exits 0 even if some removals failed.

1: No operand was given.

.SH SEE ALSO
mkdir(1), rm(1)
